---
import BaseLayout from '../../components/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHero from '../../components/PageHero.astro';
import { site } from '../../config/site';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy policy for the Joe Rossi Umpires Hall of Fame website and its online services."
  canonicalPath="/privacy-policy/"
  breadcrumbs={[{ name: 'Home', path: '/' }, { name: 'Privacy Policy', path: '/privacy-policy/' }]}
>
  <div class="page-shell">
    <PageHero title="Privacy Policy" intro={`How ${site.legalName} handles information connected with the ${site.name} website.`} />
    <section class="section">
      <article class="page-surface prose policy-copy">
        <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> June 26, 2026</p>

        <h2>Who publishes this site</h2>
        <p>This website is published by {site.legalName} for the {site.name}. The organization’s EIN is {site.ein}.</p>

        <h2>Information we may collect</h2>
        <p>The Joe Rossi Umpires Hall of Fame may collect information you choose to provide through contact forms, event inquiries, biography correction requests, photo or historical material submissions, donation or sponsorship questions, and related correspondence.</p>
        <p>Donation, payment, event registration, and sponsorship information may be processed by approved external providers such as Stripe or Eventbrite. JRHOF.org does not directly collect or store full payment card details.</p>
        <p>The site may use privacy-conscious analytics, search, advertising, or hosting measurement tools in approved phases, including services such as Google Analytics 4, Google Search Console, Google Ads, Cloudflare analytics, Cloudflare Zaraz, or similar tools. These tools may collect technical information such as pages visited, approximate location, device/browser information, referral sources, and interactions with donation, event, contact, or external links.</p>

        <h2>How information may be used</h2>
        <p>Information may be used to respond to inquiries, review biography or archive corrections, coordinate event questions, process donations through Stripe when enabled, maintain appropriate donor or event records, improve the website, and preserve Hall of Fame records.</p>

        <h2>Payments</h2>
        <p>Online payment card information is entered only through Stripe or another approved PCI-compliant payment processor. JRHOF.org does not request payment card numbers through contact forms or email.</p>

        <h2>Information sharing</h2>
        <p>The organization may share information with service providers that help operate the site, process donations, manage event registration, deliver email, host the website, measure site performance, or support organizational records. Examples may include Stripe, Eventbrite, Google services, Cloudflare, an approved transactional email provider, and hosting providers.</p>
        <p>The organization may also share information when needed for legal, compliance, security, or organizational governance purposes. The organization does not sell personal information.</p>

        <h2>Retention</h2>
        <p>The organization may retain submitted information for as long as needed to respond to the inquiry, preserve Hall of Fame records, maintain donor or event records, satisfy operational needs, or meet legal and accounting obligations.</p>

        <h2>Security</h2>
        <p>The organization intends to use reasonable administrative and technical safeguards for information handled through the website. No website or internet transmission can be guaranteed to be completely secure.</p>

        <h2>Children and minors</h2>
        <p>This site is intended for a general audience and does not knowingly seek personal information from children. If a parent or guardian believes a minor has submitted personal information, they may contact the organization through the contact page.</p>

        <h2>External links</h2>
        <p>The site may link to external websites, including CHSBUA, Stripe, Eventbrite, event resources, or historical materials. The organization is not responsible for the privacy practices of external sites.</p>

        <h2>Questions</h2>
        <p>For privacy questions or requests, use the <a href="/contact/">Contact page</a>. Do not send payment card numbers or sensitive financial information through the contact form.</p>
      </article>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .policy-copy { margin-inline: auto; }
</style>
